End Season

14
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,799
Er, excuse me,
back in your car, madam.

15
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,490
- The road's closed.
- Land Rover.

16
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:18,209
Empty one.

17
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:20,599
Find a space,
then find me.

18
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,120
No... Excuse me.

19
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:24,959
- Ma'am.
- Please.

20
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,669
- Can I get through?
- No, I'm sorry.

21
00:02:26,670 --> 00:02:27,979
Please,
I'll be two minutes.

22
00:02:27,980 --> 00:02:29,719
Sorry, you can't.
It's a crime scene area.

23
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,359
Well, how long do I have to wait?

24
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,660
Hello, George.

25
00:02:34,420 --> 00:02:35,900
Evening, ma'am.

26
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,950
Nice and calm.
Well done.

27
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:42,200
Tell that to the folk who are
backed up on the ring road.

28
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:44,990
He could have waited
till Sunday morning.

29
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,559
Anyone see him come down?

30
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:49,199
No-one that's come forward.

31
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:52,320
That couple there, they were
two storeys up, driving round.

32
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,170
Other than that, nothing.

33
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,900
Right.

34
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,039
- Is that the daughter?
- Yeah.

35
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,959
Was her prom night.

36
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:11,800
Thankfully, she didn't
see it. He went up top.

37
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,930
Ma'am, this is Lila.

38
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,479
Lila, this is DCI Stanhope.

39
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:20,449
Hello, love. I'm sorry.

40
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:22,880
Is it your dad...
who fell?

41
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:28,870
Right, now, listen to me, love.

42
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,170
We're going to get someone
to come and pick you up

43
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,679
but it'll be really
helpful if you could tell

44
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:38,199
my officer here
everything that happened.

45
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:40,200
Can you do that?

46
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,679
How did he fall?

47
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:46,080
Well, that's what I'm
going to find out.

48
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,120
Was he up there on his own?

49
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,479
I don't know.

50
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,360
I was in the car.

51
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,719
- They won't leave him there, will they?
- No, love.

52
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,199
There's some special officers
on their way here

53
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,870
and they're going to
be taking your dad away.

54
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,780
- It's my daughter!
- My mum.

55
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,800
- Go on, then.
- All right.

56
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,479
- What's happened?
- I didn't see it.

57
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:16,139
- Where's your dad?
- We went for chips.

58
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:18,440
- Where's your dad, luv?
- Mrs. Thorne, love.

59
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,710
You can't go through.

60
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,520
Right, here we go.

61
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:53,599
He's face up at least.

62
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,500
Check his pockets, Kenny.

63
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Parking ticket.

64
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,719
Smashed.

65
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:10,080
- See if you can get that fixed.
- Will do.

66
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,790
Awkward place to pick.

67
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,040
If he did pick it.

68
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,049
So what's with the limp?

69
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:30,759
I was playing five-a-side.

70
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,690
Dirty players, those firemen.

71
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,540
Well, that's where he paid.

72
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,839
Now this suggests he
didn't jump, doesn't it?

73
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,599
How does it suggest that?

74
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,960
Well, why would you pay for parking?

75
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:55,079
And why has he come
all the way over here?

76
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,550
Please don't do that!

77
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:02,109
Right,
make this the primary scene.

78
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:04,719
But get them to sweep the whole area.

79
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:07,119
And get them to check the outside.

80
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,919
In case he clung on.

81
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,490
Could it have been an accident?

82
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,820
Don't know.

83
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,509
Why,
what are you thinking?

84
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:18,479
Maybe he was trying to escape from
something coming towards him,

85
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,180
might chance it on the flyover.

86
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,300
Maybe...

87
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,279
He's landed head first.

88
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:30,759
That suggests he didn't just
climb over and step off.

89
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,010
- So, pushed?
- Don't know.

90
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:39,050
But from the way he landed,
I'd say he went off backwards.

91
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,879
Look at that.

92
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,750
What's he seen?
Kenny, go back.

93
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:49,039
Here, watch. Now,
he's seen something.

94
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,959
And it's not someone asking
for change, is it?

95
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,579
Are we sure it's not the daughter?

96
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:56,399
No. She said she was in the
car on the floor below.

97
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,839
Are there any other cameras
covering this area?

98
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:02,359
No. They only coverage is on the
entry barrier and payment machines.

99
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:05,059
You've ruled out everyone
else in the vicinity?

100
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:08,149
- Yes, we have.
- So if someone came on foot,

101
00:07:08,150 --> 00:07:09,599
like up the stairs,

102
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,699
they wouldn't necessarily
be seen on here?

103
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,439
Not necessarily, no.

104
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:15,649
So how long was this
before he falls?

105
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:17,099
About five minutes.

106
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,159
According to one of the drivers,
said he landed on the car.

107
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:22,410
So, he sees something,
he hurries towards it,

108
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:26,899
something happens
and over he goes.

109
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:28,450
Got to be linked.

110
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,159
Get uniform asking questions,

111
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,910
and I want a trace on every
car coming in and going out.

112
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,080
We've missed someone.

113
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,909
What's that?

114
00:07:40,910 --> 00:07:43,599
Windscreen wiper. Severed an artery.

115
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:46,439
Might have killed him if
he hadn't landed head first.

116
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:49,639
Does head first suggest pushed?

117
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,199
Not necessarily.

118
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,479
It suggests he didn't step off.

119
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,829
But... He could've dived.

120
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:59,079
I've seen that before. Like
they're going into water.

121
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:02,680
No, he'd have hit the flyover.

122
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,159
Were there any signs
of an altercation?

123
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,240
No, no defensive injuries.

124
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:11,390
So if he was pushed,

125
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:14,639
it wasn't off
the back of a fight.

126
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:15,999
No.

127
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:19,039
And there were no other injuries
sustained tonight.

128
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,040
However, there are these.

129
00:08:22,290 --> 00:08:23,799
How long have they been there?

130
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,159
Within the last month.

131
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:27,079
What does that suggest? That shape.

132
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:29,159
That he fell backwards
onto something solid.

133
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:32,019
Or was pushed backwards
onto something solid?

134
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:34,010
"Made contact with".

135
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:36,419
That's as certain
as I can be for now.

136
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:38,859
He'd been drinking. Couple
of glasses of red tonight

137
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:41,359
but I'd say more than
that on a regular basis.

138
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:44,319
What, problem drinker
or just your average?

139
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,399
Depends on your
definition of average.

140
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,359
He was definitely over
the limit to drive.

141
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:50,000
But went out anyway.

142
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:53,160
But that tells us something.

143
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,900
Don't know what...

144
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,959
- Hi.
- DCI Vera Stanhope.

145
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:29,659
You're...
Cameron, is that right?

146
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:32,459
- Yeah. Do you need me?
- Is your mam in?

147
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:34,759
She's just gone to bed. Could
you come back in a bit?

148
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:38,050
Yeah, well, we would, love.
It's just...

149
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:41,820
It's best if it's still
fresh in the mind.

150
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:50,600
Why did your dad pick you
up early from the prom?

151
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:56,359
I didn't get the message
till after my class.

152
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,119
Her form teacher rang.

153
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,820
Owen picked it up first.

154
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:03,060
Why did your teacher ring?

155
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:06,220
Just some girls in my class.

156
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:10,159
- You know, saying stuff.
- It's just comments.

157
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,930
We've been dealing with it.

158
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,249
Hey, you've done so well.

159
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:17,000
Did you see anyone else around?

160
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,290
I didn't see anything.

161
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,790
What did you get
up to last night?

162
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,040
I was round my mate Greg's.

163
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:34,350
Yeah, I came back just ahead
of my mum and the police.

164
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,450
I'll give you his number.

165
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:40,390
Would your dad normally
stay in on a Saturday?

166
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:43,060
Yeah.

167
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:47,220
Sometimes he went down the Ship,
but not that much recently.

168
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,580
He was trying not to drink.

169
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,230
Had he made plans for the weekend?

170
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:56,719
There was talk of bowling today.

171
00:10:56,720 --> 00:11:00,699
And on Mondays he goes down
to the beach and cleans up.

172
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:03,199
Some eco project thing.

173
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:07,319
No signs of depression or...
previous attempts?

174
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:09,660
No, nothing.

175
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,460
Nothing like that.

176
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,100
He just wouldn't of.

177
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,659
He weren't the type.

178
00:11:16,660 --> 00:11:20,470
Did you get a sense he was under
stress at all, at work maybe?

179
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:24,450
Management were on his back
for a while, I know that.

180
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,719
But he said it'd blown over.

181
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,039
What did he do?

182
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,960
- Worked at the docks, didn't he?
- Yeah.

183
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,800
What about longer-term plans?

184
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:39,900
Well, there's Lila, obviously,
and they were adopting her.

185
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,560
Right, how long has she
been with your mum and dad?

186
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,380
Three years.

187
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:52,160
Will that still happen, the adoption?

188
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,960
- This won't delay it, will it?
- I don't know.

189
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,750
I can't think that it would.

190
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:08,050
I feel like I should be doing
something, but I don't know what.

191
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:16,039
We found some bruising
on your husband's body.

192
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:18,810
Do you know what that might be from?

193
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,700
Yeah.

194
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:27,190
He fell over, coming out of the Ship,
the pub, about three week ago.

195
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:30,870
Not like drunk, just like accidental.

196
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,370
I think that's what he said.

197
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:40,440
We might also have to look
at the possibility...

198
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:45,350
.. that someone else was involved
in your husband's death.

199
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:52,500
What, like some random
person just knocked him?

200
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:57,119
- Like who?
- Had he fallen out with anyone?

201
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,420
No.

202
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,880
Not that I know of.

203
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:05,959
Did Helen speak to
anyone from the docks?

204
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:08,239
Yeah. They're having
a do in his honour.

205
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:11,180
Right, so was well liked.

206
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:14,790
Also, Lila.
She's fostered.

207
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,820
- Is she?
- They're going to adopt her.

208
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:24,490
Right, so can we dig with
the family services?

209
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,500
Right, get Helen onto that an' all.

210
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:31,059
So not apparently suicidal,

211
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:32,959
no known disputes.

212
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,119
Where are we on the CCTV trawl?

213
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:37,159
Still trawling the CCTV.

214
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,519
Is that his phone records?

215
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:41,279
Not yet, but we had a print
match come up from the body.

216
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,199
Community picked up
a bloke after a fight

217
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,599
on Bloomfield Street
about three weeks back.

218
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,299
So, could that be the
bruising on his back?

219
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:51,500
Could be. Except this bloke was
calling himself Owen Pearson.

220
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:55,200
This is Owen Thorne, right?

221
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:57,240
Yeah, it is.

222
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:00,569
- Anything on the other fella in the ruck?
- No.

223
00:14:00,570 --> 00:14:04,079
So he's lied to the
police about his ID.

224
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,439
Why would he do that?

225
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,549
He told the police the
fight was his fault.

226
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:10,559
"Was just a bar room debate.
Got out of hand."

227
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:14,759
So he drinks, he fights, he
lies to his wife about it.

228
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,309
Now, that's not exactly the picture

229
00:14:16,310 --> 00:14:18,360
we're getting from home, is it?

230
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,780
Ma'am.

231
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:30,220
- Where was the fight?
- Just on the corner there.

232
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,950
I think you should come in.
It's a good turnout.

233
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:37,859
Popular, then.

234
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:40,020
Company's put some
money behind the bar.

235
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,209
Hi. What can I get you?

236
00:14:44,210 --> 00:14:45,510
Don't tempt me, love.

237
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:49,950
No, we're investigating
the death of Owen Thorne.

238
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:52,359
- Right.
- Did you know him?

239
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,649
Yeah. He's been coming
in here for years.

240
00:14:54,650 --> 00:14:56,370
When was he last in?

241
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,619
He hasn't been in for a while.

242
00:14:58,620 --> 00:15:01,159
What, not since the fight out front?

243
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,930
Don't know about a fight.

244
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,750
Ask them.

245
00:15:08,180 --> 00:15:10,729
I know no-one wants to speak ill

246
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:13,850
but, come on, lads,
a man's died.

247
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:17,300
- That's why we've turned up.
- Not for the free bar?

248
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:24,799
All right, let's start
with the scrap outside.

249
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,100
Anyone see it?

250
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:32,720
You might save us getting the wrong
end of the stick, that's all.

251
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:37,359
Did he do something
we should know about?

252
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:40,250
No, the opposite.

253
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:45,650
His mind wasn't on the job...

254
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,150
and there was an accident.

255
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,670
March back.

256
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:54,550
He didn't check the safety
equipment and a lad died.

257
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:58,070
- And you think...?
- Blood on his hands,

258
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:00,550
to call a spade a spade.

259
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:06,679
Anyone else feel like this?

260
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:08,279
Not anyone.

261
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,580
Everyone.

262
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,699
Owen Thorne fell to his death

263
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:23,769
from the top of Eastgate car park.

264
00:16:23,770 --> 00:16:26,339
Now, there's some
indication he encountered

265
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:29,019
an as yet unidentified
person or persons

266
00:16:29,020 --> 00:16:30,619
shortly before his death.

267
00:16:30,620 --> 00:16:32,889
Now, the trajectory of his fall

268
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:34,979
suggests he fell backwards.

269
00:16:34,980 --> 00:16:36,789
But his injuries
are not conclusive

270
00:16:36,790 --> 00:16:39,149
with him having been pushed.
But until we know otherwise,

271
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:41,219
we're treating his
death as suspicious.

272
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:43,519
Now, have we got a less grisly photo?

273
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:45,459
Something that gives
a sense of the man...

274
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:47,019
Selfie from the daughter.

275
00:16:47,020 --> 00:16:49,009
Taken and posted
on social media

276
00:16:49,010 --> 00:16:51,090
about 20 minutes
before death.

277
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:54,439
Well, he looks happy
enough, doesn't he?

278
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:55,740
They both do.

279
00:16:56,980 --> 00:17:00,229
Now, the family seem to
think everything was fine.

280
00:17:00,230 --> 00:17:02,129
But preliminary inquiries

281
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:04,249
suggest his colleagues
blamed him

282
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:05,969
for a fatal accident at work.

283
00:17:05,970 --> 00:17:09,289
Young lad called Tom
McKittrick, killed in March.

284
00:17:09,290 --> 00:17:11,419
Helen, did you get on
to the docks management?

285
00:17:11,420 --> 00:17:13,909
Yeah, they're saying
we need to speak to HSE.

286
00:17:13,910 --> 00:17:15,899
- I get the impression they're...
- Stonewalling.

287
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:18,259
- Yep.
- Right, let's get down there.

288
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:21,599
Get a bit awkward, see if we
can talk to the lad's family.

289
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:24,259
So is that our line of enquiry?
Linked to this lad's death?

290
00:17:24,260 --> 00:17:26,159
Till we've got something better.

291
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:28,299
Argument over a parking space.

292
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:29,609
That'll be it.

293
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:31,579
Very emotive, parking.

294
00:17:31,580 --> 00:17:33,789
Now, where are we on his phone?

295
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:36,229
They got the SIM out.
We're waiting for the provider.

296
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:38,019
Right.
Hey, where are you going?

297
00:17:38,020 --> 00:17:40,819
You stay here. Get
that leg up, Hopalong.

298
00:17:40,820 --> 00:17:42,219
Kenny, you're with me.

299
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:44,729
Family services want to know

300
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:48,139
if we judge the home to be "a
suitable environment" for Lila?

301
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:49,659
Suitable, how?

302
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:51,319
I think what they're
driving at is,

303
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,150
are the family under suspicion?

304
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,289
Are they?
What about the son, Cameron?

305
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:58,459
Have we verified he
was with his mate?

306
00:17:58,460 --> 00:18:00,179
Uniform are there as we speak.

307
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:03,619
- Is he adopted?
- Yeah. And they've also fostered quite a few.

308
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:05,779
That's why they're asking
us before piling in.

309
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:08,559
Right, and what about Mam?
Where was she on the night?

310
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:10,379
Hattington Leisure Centre.

311
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,379
Dance instructor's coming
in to give a statement.

312
00:18:12,380 --> 00:18:15,229
Right. So are they
under suspicion or...?

313
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:16,539
Well...

314
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:21,379
Tell the truth: at the present time,
the family are not under suspicion.

315
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:22,680
OK.

316
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:24,820
Right.

317
00:18:28,660 --> 00:18:30,359
Head office haven't rung me.

318
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,750
Oh, we didn't tell them
we were coming, love.

319
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:36,179
You should really speak
to someone from London.

320
00:18:36,180 --> 00:18:38,969
We just want to see his office,

321
00:18:38,970 --> 00:18:42,419
see if we can get an idea
of his day to day, you know.

322
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:43,880
Are his family OK?

323
00:18:44,860 --> 00:18:46,160
Very shocked.

324
00:18:47,340 --> 00:18:49,059
I would send a card, only...

325
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:51,350
Well, what do you say?

326
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:53,200
Right.

327
00:18:53,820 --> 00:18:55,710
He was only in Friday.

328
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:59,200
Was he... himself?

329
00:19:00,380 --> 00:19:03,019
I'd say he's definitely
been quieter recently.

330
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:06,120
But maybe there was a
lot going on at home.

331
00:19:07,460 --> 00:19:09,380
And what about at work?

332
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:13,890
There was a fatality on
his watch, wasn't there?

333
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:17,509
You'd have to ask head office.
I'm not across the case.

334
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:19,390
If you can just give us the basics.

335
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:23,259
A lad,
Tom McKittrick,

336
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:25,399
got trapped under a crate.

337
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:28,109
His side tried to make
out the rig was faulty.

338
00:19:28,110 --> 00:19:30,219
And "his side" being?

339
00:19:30,220 --> 00:19:32,510
There's been a compo case.
Finished last month.

340
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:35,659
They tried to say it was dodgy,

341
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:37,659
but all the safety
checks were sound and...

342
00:19:37,660 --> 00:19:40,459
And was it Owen's job
to do the safety checks?

343
00:19:40,460 --> 00:19:43,300
Yes. Sign them off and log them
on the system, which he did.

344
00:19:43,660 --> 00:19:45,299
That's why they found in our favour.

345
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:46,600
That and...

346
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:50,560
And what?

347
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:56,739
They found cannabis in Tom's blood.

348
00:19:56,740 --> 00:19:58,699
After he died.

349
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:01,419
I'm not saying he was at fault but...

350
00:20:01,420 --> 00:20:05,200
So, why are the people
here blaming Owen?

351
00:20:06,420 --> 00:20:07,939
Tom's dad,

352
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:09,240
Mick,

353
00:20:09,660 --> 00:20:12,939
he's been here years. People
might have listened.

354
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:15,459
And is this Mick here today?

355
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:17,650
No.
He left in June.

356
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:21,720
I think the polite word is breakdown.

357
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:31,939
So how does Mick's
compo being refused

358
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:35,460
tally timewise with that fight
outside the dockers' pub?

359
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:37,979
I think it was the day after.

360
00:20:37,980 --> 00:20:39,859
So likely to be linked.

361
00:20:39,860 --> 00:20:41,160
Aye, maybe.

362
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,859
Didn't get the money,
lost his rag.

363
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:47,380
A dry run for Saturday night.

364
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:08,790
Mick McKittrick?

365
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:11,219
- Yeah.
- Need to talk to you, love.

366
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:12,950
- DCI...
- Is this about Tom?

367
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:15,250
Have you found summat?

368
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:21,539
Is she all right?

369
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:22,840
His Ellie.

370
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:25,350
Shocked, I think.

371
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,000
That'll be tough for her.

372
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:32,550
I know how that one feels.

373
00:21:35,220 --> 00:21:36,659
Why do you need me?

374
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:38,889
Well, it's our understanding

375
00:21:38,890 --> 00:21:41,979
that you blamed Owen
for the death of your son.

376
00:21:41,980 --> 00:21:43,339
I do, yeah.

377
00:21:43,340 --> 00:21:45,919
- Yeah, I did.
- Can I ask why?

378
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:47,539
Look, Tom knew what he was doing.

379
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:50,040
So it stands to reason the
equipment wasn't right.

380
00:21:52,220 --> 00:21:54,779
He'd watched me do
it since he was a kid.

381
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:57,350
Then why did the company say
that the check had been done?

382
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,150
They would, wouldn't they?

383
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:06,039
He'd been slacking off for
months, was common knowledge.

384
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:08,119
Why do you think the
lads are all on my side?

385
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:12,980
- In what way slacking off?
- I don't know. He'd checked out.

386
00:22:13,580 --> 00:22:15,520
His mind was elsewhere.

387
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:19,989
15 years I've known him
and he wouldn't admit it.

388
00:22:19,990 --> 00:22:22,480
Pulled rank on me,
lied to my face.

389
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:26,850
I deserved better than that.

390
00:22:27,860 --> 00:22:30,609
- Did you have a ruck about it?
- No.

391
00:22:30,610 --> 00:22:33,269
What about outside the Ship
about three weeks back?

392
00:22:33,270 --> 00:22:34,570
No.

393
00:22:35,380 --> 00:22:38,020
What about Saturday
night? Where were you?

394
00:22:41,340 --> 00:22:42,640
I was at home.

395
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:47,800
Up Jacob's Creek
without a paddle.

396
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:55,930
I'll get Mick's phone checked
out, and his car.

397
00:22:57,380 --> 00:23:01,059
Get the CSOs that cautioned
the fight brought in.

398
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:02,810
We'll do an ID.

399
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:08,639
Now,
Owen...

400
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:11,899
told community the
fight was his fault, right?

401
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:13,200
Yeah.

402
00:23:14,020 --> 00:23:16,249
Now,
if Mick had gone for him outside

403
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:18,510
that pub and Owen didn't say...

404
00:23:19,620 --> 00:23:23,530
could that be because he felt
guilty about the cover-up?

405
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:26,360
Maybe.

406
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:28,990
Explains why he took the blame.

407
00:23:29,420 --> 00:23:32,139
- Possibility, isn't it?
- Yeah.

408
00:23:32,140 --> 00:23:34,739
Maybe that's why
he didn't mention

409
00:23:34,740 --> 00:23:37,590
the accident to his family.
Couldn't look 'em in the eye.

410
00:23:38,540 --> 00:23:42,319
Bring the family back in.
Let's get a formal statement.

411
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:46,339
And get on to HSE, see if you can
clock anything they've missed.

412
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:49,900
No, not the crack team
from the safety squad?

413
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:53,119
Voil×.
Owen's phone.

414
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:55,689
- Good as new.
- Get anything off it?

415
00:23:55,690 --> 00:23:57,299
Seven calls from
a withheld number

416
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:59,610
within the 10 minutes
prior to his death.

417
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:03,050
So someone was badgering him.

418
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:08,849
Right, see if you can trace that
withheld number. Top priority.

419
00:24:08,850 --> 00:24:12,210
Oh, no, hang on. Kenny, give
me McKittrick's phone.

420
00:24:15,420 --> 00:24:16,939
Right.

421
00:24:16,940 --> 00:24:19,250
Let's see if Owen's on here.

422
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:23,000
Yep.

423
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:27,739
Mick McKittrick.

424
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:30,350
So it wasn't Mick ringing
him on the night.

425
00:24:31,620 --> 00:24:32,979
What about texts?

426
00:24:32,980 --> 00:24:35,309
Deleted from the handset.
Getting them from the server.

427
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:37,320
He cleared his handset?

428
00:24:38,740 --> 00:24:40,940
Well, what was he up to?

429
00:24:41,740 --> 00:24:44,820
Eye off the ball at work,
drinking,

430
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:48,150
family all saying
"Nothing to see here".

431
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,899
Did we place Cameron
at his mate's house?

432
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:55,699
Yeah. Greg confirmed and the
neighbours saw him returning,

433
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:58,050
shortly before we arrived
with the mum and his sister.

434
00:25:02,060 --> 00:25:03,530
Do you want something?

435
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:07,579
Sorry... Bethany said to come
as soon as I found anything.

436
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:10,979
Well, I've been trawling
through the street CCTV.

437
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:12,280
Right.

438
00:25:14,300 --> 00:25:15,979
Yeah, that's Owen.

439
00:25:15,980 --> 00:25:18,739
- Who's the other fella?
- I don't know.

440
00:25:18,740 --> 00:25:21,950
Well, get this blown up,
see if uniform can get an ID.

441
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:25,259
I know him!

442
00:25:25,260 --> 00:25:27,469
Logan Tilley. Drug dealer.

443
00:25:27,470 --> 00:25:30,499
Minor league.
More a delivery boy than a player.

444
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:33,419
Well, Owen didn't have anything
in his bloodstream, did he?

445
00:25:33,420 --> 00:25:34,720
No.

446
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:38,300
So what's his business
with our victim?

447
00:25:57,900 --> 00:25:59,650
Anyone?
Police!

448
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:05,579
- Right, put a call out for him.
- Ma'am.

449
00:26:05,580 --> 00:26:08,020
Oi, I've got my eye on that!

450
00:26:10,540 --> 00:26:14,100
Hi, it's me. Can you get me
an all-points on Logan Tilley?

451
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:20,559
Right,
uniform are out looking for him,

452
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:23,449
but there's been a development
on Mick McKittrick.

453
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:25,719
He's used his
travel pass on a bus

454
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:28,299
from Hattington to Newcastle
about 6pm.

455
00:26:28,300 --> 00:26:30,019
So, he lied about where he was.

456
00:26:30,020 --> 00:26:33,300
And we can place him in Newcastle
at the same time as Owen.

457
00:26:34,060 --> 00:26:36,660
And I felt sorry for him an' all.

458
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:38,700
Here we go.

459
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:40,650
There he is.

460
00:27:04,740 --> 00:27:06,310
Just take him through.

461
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:12,399
What's his excuse for lying to us?

462
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:15,120
Riding the buses
to save on heating.
Said he forgot.

463
00:27:19,380 --> 00:27:22,490
You weren't at home. We know
that. So where were you?

464
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:26,810
Come on,
it's for your own sake.

465
00:27:29,660 --> 00:27:32,009
Look, you're well
known to have a grudge,

466
00:27:32,010 --> 00:27:33,609
so we've got our motive.

467
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:35,999
So, come on, Mick,
stop me chasing my tail.

468
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,580
Where were you?

469
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:46,050
I valet cars,
near the station.

470
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:52,359
I've started claiming disability,
so I didn't want to say.

471
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:55,390
Ooh, taking advantage of
the great British taxpayer?

472
00:27:57,100 --> 00:27:59,750
They've cut the legal
aid. I'm desperate.

473
00:28:02,580 --> 00:28:06,480
I thought I'd pay the money
back when I got the compo.

474
00:28:09,900 --> 00:28:12,579
So, check out the car wash.

475
00:28:12,580 --> 00:28:15,639
And while you're at it, take
in my motor. There's a love.

476
00:28:15,640 --> 00:28:17,599
Get 'em to pull a hoover through.

477
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,280
Keys are in my coat.

478
00:28:19,620 --> 00:28:21,839
- What have we got?
- Logan's file.

479
00:28:21,840 --> 00:28:24,099
No violence.
Mainly drug offences.

480
00:28:24,100 --> 00:28:25,929
Intent to supply,
possession.

481
00:28:25,930 --> 00:28:28,389
Court appearance
for child neglect?

482
00:28:28,390 --> 00:28:29,699
Yeah.

483
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:32,259
Lost custody in March 2012

484
00:28:32,260 --> 00:28:34,669
after child was left home alone.

485
00:28:34,670 --> 00:28:37,930
Currently in...
foster care.

486
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,840
That's Lila's dad, isn't it?

487
00:29:01,900 --> 00:29:04,250
Just bumped into him
while I was getting chips.

488
00:29:05,860 --> 00:29:07,160
OK.

489
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:11,499
So why didn't you mention it, hm?

490
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:13,179
I thought I did.

491
00:29:13,180 --> 00:29:14,480
No.

492
00:29:17,050 --> 00:29:19,369
Did you speak to him yourself, love?

493
00:29:19,370 --> 00:29:21,010
Dad...
Owen...

494
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,789
- wouldn't let me.
- Why not?

495
00:29:23,790 --> 00:29:25,970
Just knew I'd get upset again.

496
00:29:31,180 --> 00:29:33,450
You didn't know she'd seen him.

497
00:29:33,860 --> 00:29:35,950
She hadn't mentioned it...

498
00:29:36,740 --> 00:29:38,570
but she's traumatised.

499
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:40,750
Maybe that's why.

500
00:29:41,260 --> 00:29:43,339
Had she been in touch with him?

501
00:29:43,340 --> 00:29:46,440
No.
We'd have come down on that.

502
00:29:48,900 --> 00:29:50,980
Does she ever conceal things?

503
00:29:52,100 --> 00:29:53,400
No.

504
00:29:54,580 --> 00:29:56,250
Not any more.

505
00:29:56,940 --> 00:30:00,849
Since we've had her,
she's a changed girl.

506
00:30:00,850 --> 00:30:04,450
Responsible, kind, confident.

507
00:30:05,700 --> 00:30:08,150
That's why we're so proud of her.

508
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:13,429
- Had you been in regular contact?
- No.

509
00:30:13,430 --> 00:30:14,899
Not at all.

510
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:17,109
So when did you last see him?

511
00:30:17,110 --> 00:30:18,660
You know, prior to the chippy.

512
00:30:20,060 --> 00:30:21,820
When I got to the prom...

513
00:30:23,100 --> 00:30:25,300
Logan was waiting for me.

514
00:30:27,420 --> 00:30:30,100
Said he wanted to see me in my dress.

515
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:32,680
Take me in.

516
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:38,779
Dads weren't even supposed
to be there.

517
00:30:38,780 --> 00:30:41,530
Owen would have come
if they were.

518
00:30:42,700 --> 00:30:46,279
Anyway,
he started slagging off Owen,

519
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:48,919
saying he didn't care
about me and stuff.

520
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:52,080
I got upset,
he left.

521
00:30:52,860 --> 00:30:56,650
My form teacher rang
and Owen picked me up.

522
00:30:57,380 --> 00:31:00,209
Do you think he followed
you to the car park?

523
00:31:00,210 --> 00:31:01,539
I don't know.
But...

524
00:31:01,540 --> 00:31:03,169
He wants me to live with him.

525
00:31:03,170 --> 00:31:05,999
He's not going to do something
that gets himself in trouble.

526
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,939
- Do you want to live with him?
- No.

527
00:31:07,940 --> 00:31:09,989
I want them to adopt me.

528
00:31:09,990 --> 00:31:11,870
They're the ones that love me.

529
00:31:12,220 --> 00:31:13,750
He doesn't.

530
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:18,840
Lila,
if you've not been in contact,

531
00:31:20,030 --> 00:31:22,460
how did he know about the prom?

532
00:31:23,180 --> 00:31:26,419
He looks at my feed.
All the time.

533
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:27,720
Makes comments.

534
00:31:28,940 --> 00:31:31,340
He just won't leave me alone.

535
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:35,520
"Best night ever!"

536
00:31:36,500 --> 00:31:38,619
"Best family ever."

537
00:31:38,620 --> 00:31:40,839
Told uniform it was
to send a message

538
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,569
to the girls in her form.

539
00:31:42,570 --> 00:31:45,449
Send a message to her
dad more like.

540
00:31:45,450 --> 00:31:47,859
Not exactly to rub
his nose in it

541
00:31:47,860 --> 00:31:49,519
but to make her point.

542
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:50,820
Poor lass.

543
00:31:53,460 --> 00:31:56,950
Hold it. That one's
taken at the car park.

544
00:31:57,620 --> 00:31:59,220
So if Logan saw that,

545
00:31:59,860 --> 00:32:02,500
he could have tracked
them to the car park.

546
00:32:03,820 --> 00:32:06,689
Well, I'm banned from the
city centre, aren't I?

547
00:32:06,690 --> 00:32:09,349
- I've got an ASBO on me.
- Well, you broke that.

548
00:32:09,350 --> 00:32:12,559
You tracked your daughter to
her school dance, city centre,

549
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:15,219
and you were caught
on CCTV in the alley,

550
00:32:15,220 --> 00:32:17,419
back of Castle Street chippy.

551
00:32:17,420 --> 00:32:20,739
Right, so I'm not allowed
to eat chips now?

552
00:32:20,740 --> 00:32:23,759
Where you had an altercation
with Owen Thorne.

553
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:25,579
- So?
- So,

554
00:32:25,580 --> 00:32:28,450
So, he was found dead
20 minutes later.

555
00:32:29,860 --> 00:32:31,610
I didn't know that.

556
00:32:32,300 --> 00:32:34,640
Is Lila all right?

557
00:32:35,060 --> 00:32:36,630
Not really.

558
00:32:37,020 --> 00:32:39,759
Well, does that mean they
won't get to adopt her?

559
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:41,580
Is that what you want it to mean?

560
00:32:44,260 --> 00:32:46,450
Why did you go and see her?

561
00:32:47,580 --> 00:32:50,959
I just wanted to say goodbye
before the adoption, that's all.

562
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,619
To see her in her prom dress.

563
00:32:52,620 --> 00:32:56,299
Why? Last time you had a contact
appointment, you failed to turn up.

564
00:32:56,300 --> 00:32:58,719
But that's because I had
to sign this thing in.

565
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:00,339
See,
they screwed me over.

566
00:33:00,340 --> 00:33:02,679
I asked for an appointment
I could make.

567
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:05,620
What did you say to
Owen in the alley?

568
00:33:06,140 --> 00:33:09,940
I just wanted to apologise
to my daughter, that's all.

569
00:33:10,540 --> 00:33:12,680
I know I upset her.

570
00:33:14,460 --> 00:33:16,650
But he sent me packing,

571
00:33:17,620 --> 00:33:19,590
made me look daft.

572
00:33:20,180 --> 00:33:23,570
And he loved that, didn't he?
A power trip.

573
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:26,439
- And you just left it at that, did you?
- Yeah.

574
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:30,320
I called him a filthy pervert
and then I went on my way.

575
00:33:32,140 --> 00:33:33,720
I mean,

576
00:33:34,730 --> 00:33:38,110
what kind of a man wants to live
with other people's children, hm?

577
00:33:41,260 --> 00:33:43,739
Look,
he's got her sucked in.

578
00:33:43,740 --> 00:33:46,059
Just take a look at
her Facebook page.

579
00:33:46,060 --> 00:33:48,859
It's all "Best ever dad!"

580
00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:51,020
But they don't love her like I do.

581
00:33:51,900 --> 00:33:53,479
They're not her blood.

582
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:58,459
And did you love her when you left
her without food for days on end,

583
00:33:58,460 --> 00:34:00,800
whilst you went on a bender?

584
00:34:05,260 --> 00:34:07,260
I had an illness.

585
00:34:07,780 --> 00:34:10,900
When she's older, she'll understand.

586
00:34:11,420 --> 00:34:14,289
Right,
arrest him on suspicion of murder

587
00:34:14,290 --> 00:34:15,969
and get him a solicitor.

588
00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:18,779
Get DNA swabs couriered
over to Marcus.

589
00:34:18,780 --> 00:34:21,479
And get a blood test done.
Let's see if he's clean.

590
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:22,789
- Got all that?
- Got it.

591
00:34:22,790 --> 00:34:26,059
Right, now, we are moving
our focus to this fella,

592
00:34:26,060 --> 00:34:29,299
Logan Tilley.
That's Lila's father.

593
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:32,919
Now, possible motive:
an argument over Lila.

594
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:35,459
Maybe trying to scupper
the adoption altogether.

595
00:34:35,460 --> 00:34:36,819
That was the tagging company.

596
00:34:36,820 --> 00:34:38,879
Good. Can they place
Tilley at the car park?

597
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:41,629
No. Their GPS puts
Tilley in Morrisons

598
00:34:41,630 --> 00:34:44,820
at the same time Owen's putting
money in the machine.

599
00:34:50,460 --> 00:34:51,760
Right.

600
00:34:53,940 --> 00:34:56,509
OK.
Change of plan,

601
00:34:56,510 --> 00:34:59,089
don't arrest him on
suspicion of murder.

602
00:34:59,090 --> 00:35:01,050
Caution him for breaking the ASBO.

603
00:35:01,780 --> 00:35:04,520
Well, we're back to square
one, then, aren't we?

604
00:35:06,620 --> 00:35:09,869
Ma'am. Ma'am.
Mobile data's come through.

605
00:35:09,870 --> 00:35:13,019
The victim's last text was
to someone called Hannah.

606
00:35:13,020 --> 00:35:14,329
Hannah who?

607
00:35:14,330 --> 00:35:17,430
He says, "Sorry, can't make it
tonight. Bit under the weather."

608
00:35:18,340 --> 00:35:20,430
"Under the weather"?

609
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:26,980
Well, no-one else has mentioned Owen
being under the weather, have they?

610
00:35:27,700 --> 00:35:30,399
So is that before
or after the message

611
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:32,339
to pick up Lila from the prom?

612
00:35:32,340 --> 00:35:35,780
It's before. Hannah
replies "No worries."

613
00:35:36,140 --> 00:35:39,400
And a photo comes
up with her contact.

614
00:35:40,940 --> 00:35:43,729
Right, well, ring her.

615
00:35:43,730 --> 00:35:47,380
- Let's get her in.
- Phone's out of service.

616
00:35:48,140 --> 00:35:49,780
Sim's been taken out.

617
00:35:55,780 --> 00:35:57,080
Hannah...

618
00:36:22,780 --> 00:36:24,829
Is this about Logan?

619
00:36:24,830 --> 00:36:26,179
No.

620
00:36:26,180 --> 00:36:29,159
No, we're no longer treating
him as a suspect.

621
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,469
See?

622
00:36:30,470 --> 00:36:32,799
It were never going to
be your fault. Never.

623
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:34,420
You got that?

624
00:36:34,900 --> 00:36:37,700
We were wondering if
you could ID someone.

625
00:36:39,300 --> 00:36:41,429
I don't know her.
Who is she?

626
00:36:41,430 --> 00:36:43,430
Just someone we're trying to trace.

627
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,300
Why?

628
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:52,480
How about you, pet?

629
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:56,320
No, I don't recognise her.

630
00:36:57,860 --> 00:37:02,249
Well, we think your husband
was in communication with her

631
00:37:02,250 --> 00:37:03,999
just before he died.

632
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,699
Now, did he tell you
he was meeting anyone?

633
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:09,059
No. He said he was staying in.

634
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:12,179
Is it possible he could
have lied about that?

635
00:37:12,180 --> 00:37:13,930
Or changed his plans?

636
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:15,789
Maybe.

637
00:37:15,790 --> 00:37:18,100
If he had a good reason, I suppose.

638
00:37:20,460 --> 00:37:23,280
Cam, is this girl a friend of yours?

639
00:37:25,060 --> 00:37:27,509
No. No.
She...

640
00:37:27,510 --> 00:37:31,019
She, erm... I think she volunteers
with Dad down at Jump Start.

641
00:37:31,020 --> 00:37:33,879
Right.
Well, that makes sense.

642
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:36,609
He did some mentoring.
With a homeless charity.

643
00:37:36,610 --> 00:37:38,319
Yeah. He met loads
of people down there.

644
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,629
Yeah.

645
00:37:39,630 --> 00:37:43,350
Right. Well, thanks very
much. We'll look into that.

646
00:37:58,820 --> 00:38:02,760
I did wonder if it was the same
Owen when I heard it on the radio.

647
00:38:03,580 --> 00:38:07,090
It's sad. It's really sad.

648
00:38:07,500 --> 00:38:09,510
How long did he volunteer?

649
00:38:09,820 --> 00:38:13,359
Perhaps a year, maybe longer.

650
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:14,839
He was very good.

651
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:17,249
He was quite experienced
with young people

652
00:38:17,250 --> 00:38:18,579
who were troubled.

653
00:38:18,580 --> 00:38:20,590
Did this girl volunteer with him?

654
00:38:22,820 --> 00:38:25,659
No, that's Hannah Ferris.

655
00:38:25,660 --> 00:38:27,549
She was a service user.

656
00:38:27,550 --> 00:38:28,850
Right.

657
00:38:29,220 --> 00:38:31,619
So did you pair them up?

658
00:38:31,620 --> 00:38:34,160
He brought her in to us.

659
00:38:36,860 --> 00:38:38,850
Is that what normally happens?

660
00:38:39,500 --> 00:38:41,949
No.
Normally social services

661
00:38:41,950 --> 00:38:43,859
refer care leavers.

662
00:38:43,860 --> 00:38:45,859
But she was begging, I think.

663
00:38:45,860 --> 00:38:48,379
She was in a terrible state,
weighed about six stone.

664
00:38:48,380 --> 00:38:51,189
He asked us to get her
into accommodation.

665
00:38:51,190 --> 00:38:53,219
Did that strike you as odd?

666
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:56,019
Not really. I mean, we knew him.

667
00:38:56,020 --> 00:38:58,039
She was desperate.

668
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:59,820
It seemed legitimate.

669
00:39:01,300 --> 00:39:03,000
It was, wasn't it?

670
00:39:32,380 --> 00:39:35,699
It's not exactly the five-star
treatment, is it?

671
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:37,650
If he was trying to
pull a fast one...

672
00:39:39,260 --> 00:39:41,089
She pays on time.

673
00:39:41,090 --> 00:39:43,389
Any trouble, incidents?

674
00:39:43,390 --> 00:39:45,179
No, not like some.

675
00:39:45,180 --> 00:39:48,379
- How long has she been living here?
- Been here nearly six months.

676
00:39:48,380 --> 00:39:50,179
Works funny hours.

677
00:39:50,180 --> 00:39:51,650
Doing what?

678
00:39:52,940 --> 00:39:54,249
Is she local?

679
00:39:54,250 --> 00:39:56,509
I'd say she's Mancunian
from her accent.

680
00:39:56,510 --> 00:39:57,950
Have you seen this fella?

681
00:39:59,340 --> 00:40:00,899
Aye, yeah, I have.

682
00:40:00,900 --> 00:40:02,979
Parks his Chrysler out front.

683
00:40:02,980 --> 00:40:05,359
Well, once, more than once?

684
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:07,559
Once a week maybes.

685
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:10,510
He said he was a mate but I
presumed he was, you know...

686
00:40:13,180 --> 00:40:14,750
A client.

687
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:27,590
- Hannah Ferris?
- Yeah.

688
00:40:27,940 --> 00:40:29,779
DCI Stanhope.

689
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:32,590
We're investigating the
death of Owen Thorne.

690
00:40:33,140 --> 00:40:35,359
Right, yeah.
I heard.

691
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:36,939
What do you want me for?

692
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:38,680
Could we have a little chat?

693
00:40:39,580 --> 00:40:40,880
OK.

694
00:40:41,300 --> 00:40:43,900
Could you check with my supervisor?
Only, I've had my break.

695
00:40:47,500 --> 00:40:52,059
Do you remember receiving
this text from Mr. Thorne?

696
00:40:52,060 --> 00:40:55,699
"Sorry, can't make it tonight,
bit under the weather."

697
00:40:55,700 --> 00:40:59,419
Now, that was sent
7:30 Saturday evening.

698
00:40:59,420 --> 00:41:00,890
Yeah, course.

699
00:41:02,100 --> 00:41:03,809
Why were you meeting up?

700
00:41:03,810 --> 00:41:05,699
It was my birthday.

701
00:41:05,700 --> 00:41:07,969
A bunch of us were
meeting in the pub.

702
00:41:07,970 --> 00:41:10,229
He said he might drop in
if he was in the area.

703
00:41:10,230 --> 00:41:12,239
Can we see your phone?

704
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:14,159
I lost it Saturday night.

705
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:15,889
I think it got nicked.

706
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:18,459
How did you and Owen first meet?

707
00:41:18,460 --> 00:41:20,499
This charity, Jump Start.

708
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:22,139
Now, that's not what they told us.

709
00:41:22,140 --> 00:41:23,579
Well, it was.

710
00:41:23,580 --> 00:41:25,319
I was begging.

711
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:27,449
He found me and they
sorted me out a room.

712
00:41:27,450 --> 00:41:29,019
And when was that?

713
00:41:29,020 --> 00:41:30,739
About six months back.

714
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:32,609
And you've been friends since?

715
00:41:32,610 --> 00:41:34,579
Not friends.

716
00:41:34,580 --> 00:41:36,859
We just met up every so often.

717
00:41:36,860 --> 00:41:38,910
Talk about "life skills".

718
00:41:39,580 --> 00:41:41,280
Where did you meet?

719
00:41:41,760 --> 00:41:44,139
He'd pick me up, we'd go
to coffee shops and stuff.

720
00:41:44,140 --> 00:41:46,969
- So you met at home?
- Yeah. It wasn't a big thing.

721
00:41:46,970 --> 00:41:48,689
If I'm honest, I think he was trying

722
00:41:48,690 --> 00:41:51,339
to tick a box that he'd
helped vulnerable adults.

723
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:53,919
They were adopting. Looks
good on the form.

724
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:56,450
Your landlady thought he
might have been "a client".

725
00:41:57,940 --> 00:42:00,139
No, he bloody wasn't.

726
00:42:00,140 --> 00:42:02,959
For God's sake! I'm not
some sort of crackhead.

727
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:04,699
I barely knew him, if I'm honest.

728
00:42:04,700 --> 00:42:07,219
That didn't stop you inviting
him to your birthday party.

729
00:42:07,220 --> 00:42:09,279
- I invited loads of people.
- Bit weird, isn't it?

730
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:11,789
- Man twice your age.
- It's not weird at all.

731
00:42:11,790 --> 00:42:14,240
I wasn't sleeping with him if
that's what you're getting at.

732
00:42:15,380 --> 00:42:17,979
Ask 'em. Go on, ask them.

733
00:42:17,980 --> 00:42:19,699
Ask Caz, ask Mario.

734
00:42:19,700 --> 00:42:22,159
He's my manager. He's twice my age.

735
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:23,690
They all came.

736
00:42:30,860 --> 00:42:32,939
Owen said he was sick.

737
00:42:32,940 --> 00:42:34,499
I was like, "No worries".

738
00:42:34,500 --> 00:42:35,819
Why are you even asking me?

739
00:42:35,820 --> 00:42:39,539
Well, he didn't mention to his
family that he was meeting you.

740
00:42:39,540 --> 00:42:41,419
Now,
why do you think that is?

741
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:43,190
I don't know.
Maybe...

742
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,950
he had other plans
or just forgot.

743
00:42:46,700 --> 00:42:48,459
Can I get back to it?

744
00:42:48,460 --> 00:42:51,910
Honestly, I don't know any
more about how he passed.

745
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:59,250
Where are you from originally?

746
00:43:01,100 --> 00:43:04,750
What's that accent, Manchester?

747
00:43:05,620 --> 00:43:07,350
Rochdale, but yeah.

748
00:43:08,100 --> 00:43:10,589
I had some mates come
to college up here.

749
00:43:10,590 --> 00:43:12,150
Sort of fell out with them.

750
00:43:14,740 --> 00:43:18,690
Well, we will be checking your
movements on Saturday evening.

751
00:43:22,460 --> 00:43:25,179
Look, it's not ideal, is it, pet?

752
00:43:25,180 --> 00:43:27,309
A B&B on the Longley Road.

753
00:43:27,310 --> 00:43:29,039
Can you not go home?

754
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:30,659
You got any family?

755
00:43:30,660 --> 00:43:33,020
My mum...
passed away.

756
00:43:33,940 --> 00:43:36,539
- I'm sorry.
- It's all right.

757
00:43:36,540 --> 00:43:38,210
I got back on my feet.

758
00:43:45,420 --> 00:43:48,190
Could you pass on my condolences
to Ellie and stuff?

759
00:43:48,940 --> 00:43:52,419
- He talked about his family, then?
- Yeah.

760
00:43:52,420 --> 00:43:55,479
Banged on about how love can
turn people's lives around.

761
00:43:55,480 --> 00:43:57,100
Soppy git like that.

762
00:44:04,300 --> 00:44:07,379
- Where's Bethany?
- She's double-checking alibis.

763
00:44:07,380 --> 00:44:09,249
Right. You can do it.

764
00:44:09,250 --> 00:44:11,509
Get on to the Care
System in Rochdale.

765
00:44:11,510 --> 00:44:13,369
See if they can trace Hannah Ferris.

766
00:44:13,370 --> 00:44:15,629
She says there's
nothing untoward and,

