1011
00:57:54,580 --> 00:57:55,880
Thanks.

1012
00:58:00,420 --> 00:58:03,070
That was the only thing
keeping her going.

1013
00:58:17,100 --> 00:58:19,259
Her name's Gloria Edwards.

1014
00:58:19,260 --> 00:58:21,070
Yes, I saw her.

1015
00:58:21,380 --> 00:58:23,039
She was on her own.

1016
00:58:23,040 --> 00:58:24,719
Did she make a reservation?

1017
00:58:24,720 --> 00:58:26,639
Table five is set
aside for walk-ins.

1018
00:58:26,640 --> 00:58:28,349
So probably not.

1019
00:58:28,350 --> 00:58:31,050
But she was here,
for sure.

1020
00:58:49,660 --> 00:58:51,660
Here you are.

1021
00:58:52,500 --> 00:58:54,500
Right.

1022
00:58:55,740 --> 00:58:58,979
So the day Owen
goes AWOL from work...

1023
00:58:58,980 --> 00:59:01,499
.. and he's parked outside
Mountford General,

1024
00:59:01,500 --> 00:59:03,939
there's a female admitted
under the name of Ferris

1025
00:59:03,940 --> 00:59:05,959
- for alcohol poisoning.
- Hannah?

1026
00:59:05,960 --> 00:59:08,969
Well, the patient's taken home
before she can be properly admitted.

1027
00:59:08,970 --> 00:59:11,459
So the nurse writes her
off as a time-waster.

1028
00:59:11,460 --> 00:59:14,109
But we know that Hannah
gets off her face.

1029
00:59:14,110 --> 00:59:15,859
- So...
- So?

1030
00:59:15,860 --> 00:59:18,539
I'm thinking Hannah
gets messed up.

1031
00:59:18,540 --> 00:59:20,449
She wants attention,

1032
00:59:20,450 --> 00:59:22,689
she wants him to come
running after her.

1033
00:59:22,690 --> 00:59:25,659
- What, she's pretending?
- Well, maybe it's a false alarm.

1034
00:59:25,660 --> 00:59:27,339
He gets back to work by midday.

1035
00:59:27,340 --> 00:59:29,489
But he can't tell
'em the real reason

1036
00:59:29,490 --> 00:59:31,610
why he's late for the safety
checks because...

1037
00:59:32,020 --> 00:59:34,550
- .. well, he's in a relationship.
- Right.

1038
00:59:34,860 --> 00:59:37,990
You know who she put down?
Her fancy man, as next of kin.

1039
00:59:38,500 --> 00:59:41,419
Come on, boss, even you've
got to be impressed with that.

1040
00:59:41,420 --> 00:59:45,339
I am, pet.
I am.

1041
00:59:45,340 --> 00:59:47,699
Except you're missing the obvious.

1042
00:59:47,700 --> 00:59:51,739
He's not her fancy man,
he IS her next of kin.

1043
00:59:51,740 --> 00:59:53,040
Come on!

1044
01:00:02,460 --> 01:00:05,239
My mum found his details
on the internet.

1045
01:00:05,240 --> 01:00:06,809
You said your mum was dead.

1046
01:00:06,810 --> 01:00:08,449
Before she died.

1047
01:00:08,450 --> 01:00:12,139
I found them stored on the
laptop. I came looking.

1048
01:00:12,140 --> 01:00:14,869
So all that stuff about
you begging was a lie?

1049
01:00:14,870 --> 01:00:16,679
He wanted to give
me money for rent.

1050
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:18,160
I said no.

1051
01:00:18,960 --> 01:00:20,919
But I was hard up,

1052
01:00:20,920 --> 01:00:23,380
so I let him refer me to the charity.

1053
01:00:24,180 --> 01:00:26,979
Was he glad you made contact?

1054
01:00:26,980 --> 01:00:29,870
Yeah, we had a big family party.

1055
01:00:30,780 --> 01:00:32,980
Look, I was a mess.

1056
01:00:33,420 --> 01:00:37,600
He wasn't exactly thrilled but
he wasn't made of stone either.

1057
01:00:38,980 --> 01:00:41,219
Why did you come looking?

1058
01:00:41,220 --> 01:00:43,830
I just did.
Wouldn't you?

1059
01:00:45,620 --> 01:00:48,329
I'm not saying everyone
has to be 2.4 kids.

1060
01:00:48,330 --> 01:00:50,739
But you need to know where
you come from, don't you?

1061
01:00:50,740 --> 01:00:52,699
And where do you come from?

1062
01:00:52,700 --> 01:00:54,299
A one-nighter.

1063
01:00:54,300 --> 01:00:56,149
He was quite open about that.

1064
01:00:56,150 --> 01:00:57,639
Before they adopted Cameron,

1065
01:00:57,640 --> 01:01:00,450
him and Ellie, I think,
were having a bit of a bad time.

1066
01:01:00,820 --> 01:01:03,839
I think with the fertility
treatment and all that.

1067
01:01:03,840 --> 01:01:07,799
Anyway, this one night he goes
out, gets it on with my mum.

1068
01:01:07,800 --> 01:01:11,210
Bang.
That's me, one-hit wonder.

1069
01:01:13,380 --> 01:01:16,120
You can see why he didn't
want his wife to know.

1070
01:01:16,620 --> 01:01:18,660
It's not nice, is it?

1071
01:01:22,700 --> 01:01:26,499
So he didn't actually have
a relationship with your mam?

1072
01:01:26,500 --> 01:01:28,019
No.

1073
01:01:28,020 --> 01:01:29,829
He knocked her up...

1074
01:01:29,830 --> 01:01:32,699
She asked but he wasn't interested.

1075
01:01:32,700 --> 01:01:35,939
So she moved to Manchester
to start again.

1076
01:01:35,940 --> 01:01:38,850
Got married...
for about two minutes.

1077
01:01:39,900 --> 01:01:41,979
It's like she told me.

1078
01:01:41,980 --> 01:01:45,009
Getting pregnant with
me ruined her life.

1079
01:01:45,010 --> 01:01:48,290
But, you know, I'm over it.

1080
01:01:54,620 --> 01:01:57,620
Why did she look for
him on the internet?

1081
01:01:58,580 --> 01:02:00,899
Torture herself I think.

1082
01:02:00,900 --> 01:02:03,230
She was a bit crackers if I'm honest.

1083
01:02:03,820 --> 01:02:05,940
How'd your mam die?

1084
01:02:06,660 --> 01:02:08,820
Topped herself.

1085
01:02:14,700 --> 01:02:18,710
Do you blame your dad at all?
For the rejection.

1086
01:02:20,260 --> 01:02:22,570
Not so as I'd kill him.

1087
01:02:24,700 --> 01:02:28,609
How'd you feel about him
missing your birthday, hm?

1088
01:02:28,610 --> 01:02:31,059
Something came up probably.

1089
01:02:31,060 --> 01:02:33,109
We weren't his priority.

1090
01:02:33,110 --> 01:02:35,550
Honestly, I didn't mind.

1091
01:02:36,360 --> 01:02:37,660
Right.

1092
01:02:38,240 --> 01:02:39,799
Why were you hospitalised?

1093
01:02:39,800 --> 01:02:42,059
- When?
- Few months back.

1094
01:02:42,060 --> 01:02:43,539
March.

1095
01:02:43,540 --> 01:02:46,180
No.
Don't know anything about that.

1096
01:02:51,500 --> 01:02:54,199
I'll chase the hospital,
see if she's lying.

1097
01:02:54,200 --> 01:02:56,829
Well, that doesn't alter the fact
that at the time of death

1098
01:02:56,830 --> 01:02:58,869
she was in a club with her mates.

1099
01:02:58,870 --> 01:03:01,530
Think, what does this mean?

1100
01:03:02,420 --> 01:03:04,890
Him having another kid.

1101
01:03:05,420 --> 01:03:07,819
Biological one at that.

1102
01:03:07,820 --> 01:03:12,259
It certainly gives Mam something
to be hacked off about, doesn't it?

1103
01:03:12,260 --> 01:03:13,779
Possible.

1104
01:03:13,780 --> 01:03:17,250
Let's bring her in,
do a formal interview.

1105
01:03:18,460 --> 01:03:21,259
Or should I be looking at Lila?

1106
01:03:21,260 --> 01:03:23,499
A girl that age capable of...?

1107
01:03:23,500 --> 01:03:26,900
Ma'am, this fella's
been waiting an hour.

1108
01:03:27,740 --> 01:03:29,619
It's that docker.

1109
01:03:29,620 --> 01:03:32,090
- Are you waiting for me?
- Yeah.

1110
01:03:32,980 --> 01:03:34,899
We've heard.

1111
01:03:34,900 --> 01:03:36,869
You've heard what?

1112
01:03:36,870 --> 01:03:39,159
That you've got
Mick his evidence.

1113
01:03:39,160 --> 01:03:41,219
Right, yes. Yes, we have.

1114
01:03:41,220 --> 01:03:42,750
That's good news.

1115
01:03:43,380 --> 01:03:47,120
Well, where I'm from, one
good turn deserves another.

1116
01:03:50,620 --> 01:03:52,739
I saw the fight.

1117
01:03:52,740 --> 01:03:55,169
- The fight outside the pub?
- Yeah.

1118
01:03:55,170 --> 01:03:57,429
And he wasn't being vicious.
He just...

1119
01:03:57,430 --> 01:03:59,259
pushed him and Owen
fell on his back.

1120
01:03:59,260 --> 01:04:01,019
Bang, straight on the kerb.

1121
01:04:01,020 --> 01:04:03,079
Didn't know his own strength,
I'd say.

1122
01:04:03,080 --> 01:04:05,610
Who pushed him?
Was this Mick McKittrick?

1123
01:04:06,140 --> 01:04:07,440
No.

1124
01:04:11,560 --> 01:04:15,180
It was Cameron,
his son.

1125
01:04:30,780 --> 01:04:32,259
He's not picking up his mobile.

1126
01:04:32,260 --> 01:04:35,079
This Greg definitely
vouched for Cameron?

1127
01:04:35,080 --> 01:04:37,850
- Yeah.
- Get Kenny to double-check.

1128
01:04:38,540 --> 01:04:40,699
Did you trace his
mobile on the night?

1129
01:04:40,700 --> 01:04:42,700
No, cos his friend vouched for him.

1130
01:04:49,380 --> 01:04:51,490
Lila...
Lila, love...

1131
01:04:51,900 --> 01:04:55,290
I'm looking for Cameron.
Do you know where he is, love?

1132
01:04:56,260 --> 01:04:58,139
Yeah.
He's working.

1133
01:04:58,140 --> 01:04:59,489
Great.

1134
01:04:59,490 --> 01:05:01,019
Thanks.

1135
01:05:01,020 --> 01:05:02,899
At Hattington Golf Course.

1136
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:04,200
Right.

1137
01:05:05,740 --> 01:05:07,190
Are you all right?

1138
01:05:09,900 --> 01:05:11,200
No.

1139
01:05:11,820 --> 01:05:13,120
What's up?

1140
01:05:13,740 --> 01:05:15,810
They're saying they have to move me.

1141
01:05:17,400 --> 01:05:18,700
I'm sorry.

1142
01:05:23,820 --> 01:05:25,129
I'm sorry.

1143
01:05:25,130 --> 01:05:27,459
I'm going to have to
ask you something, pet.

1144
01:05:27,460 --> 01:05:31,980
Now, did Cameron and
Owen have a falling out?

1145
01:05:32,420 --> 01:05:34,339
Within the last month.

1146
01:05:34,340 --> 01:05:37,399
Right, are you going
to ruin HIS life now?

1147
01:05:37,400 --> 01:05:40,009
No. I'm only asking
because a witness said

1148
01:05:40,010 --> 01:05:41,829
he thought they might
have had a fight.

1149
01:05:41,830 --> 01:05:43,880
- Did they?
- They did, yeah.

1150
01:05:44,460 --> 01:05:45,960
What was it about?

1151
01:05:47,100 --> 01:05:48,980
Dad was cheating on Mum.

1152
01:05:50,620 --> 01:05:52,259
With that homeless girl.

1153
01:05:52,260 --> 01:05:54,419
Saw his car outside where she lives.

1154
01:05:54,420 --> 01:05:56,179
Cam went ballistic about it.

1155
01:05:56,180 --> 01:05:58,080
Owen told him he'd got it wrong.

1156
01:05:59,180 --> 01:06:00,909
We believed him.

1157
01:06:00,910 --> 01:06:02,210
Right.

1158
01:06:04,540 --> 01:06:06,629
But you know different, don't you?

1159
01:06:06,630 --> 01:06:08,830
That's why you're looking
for her, isn't it?

1160
01:06:14,220 --> 01:06:15,699
He's on compassionate leave.

1161
01:06:15,700 --> 01:06:18,659
His sister was under the
impression he was working today.

1162
01:06:18,660 --> 01:06:21,179
Yeah, I mean, he did come on
earlier but I sent him home.

1163
01:06:21,180 --> 01:06:22,489
Why's that?

1164
01:06:22,490 --> 01:06:24,349
He were caddying for some
fellas on a corporate.

1165
01:06:24,350 --> 01:06:26,339
But he started to get upset.

1166
01:06:26,340 --> 01:06:28,059
Lost it with them,
I think.

1167
01:06:28,060 --> 01:06:29,800
Right, thanks, mate.

1168
01:06:38,300 --> 01:06:40,479
Unaccounted for since
11am this morning.

1169
01:06:40,480 --> 01:06:43,019
We need to speak to him in connection
with an assault on his dad

1170
01:06:43,020 --> 01:06:44,720
three weeks prior to the murder.

1171
01:06:53,910 --> 01:06:55,219
DCI Stanhope.

1172
01:06:55,220 --> 01:06:58,339
<i>Hello,
it's Jayne-Anne from Jump Start.</i>

1173
01:06:58,340 --> 01:07:01,299
We've had a lad in looking
for info on Hannah Ferris.

1174
01:07:01,300 --> 01:07:04,300
- Right, what did you tell him?
- Nothing. We have procedures.

1175
01:07:05,260 --> 01:07:06,719
But he was quite angry.

1176
01:07:06,720 --> 01:07:09,139
<i>I think he may have been Owen's son.</i>

1177
01:07:09,140 --> 01:07:10,440
Thanks, love.

1178
01:07:18,940 --> 01:07:22,049
Let's see if we can find
Hannah before Cameron does.

1179
01:07:22,050 --> 01:07:23,950
Bring her in as a precaution.

1180
01:07:41,020 --> 01:07:42,320
Hello?

1181
01:07:43,340 --> 01:07:44,640
Hannah?

1182
01:08:10,780 --> 01:08:12,780
He'll have seen this.

1183
01:08:14,500 --> 01:08:18,099
SEAT Leon, registration
Alpha Charlie Foxtrot.

1184
01:08:18,100 --> 01:08:20,459
Male, early twenties.

1185
01:08:20,460 --> 01:08:22,790
Possibly with Hannah Ferris.

1186
01:08:24,740 --> 01:08:26,179
- Scrap that.
- It's all right.

1187
01:08:26,180 --> 01:08:27,579
- Alone.
- It's all right.

1188
01:08:27,580 --> 01:08:30,619
We think Owen's son Cameron
has been looking for you.

1189
01:08:30,620 --> 01:08:32,429
They've found the car
but not the driver.

1190
01:08:32,430 --> 01:08:34,359
That's good.
If he's on foot it'll be easier.

1191
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:35,699
He's back in coverage.

1192
01:08:35,700 --> 01:08:38,899
- We've got him down by the docks.
- Right, get uniform down there.

1193
01:08:38,900 --> 01:08:40,339
But don't scare him off.

1194
01:08:40,340 --> 01:08:44,180
Might have a bee in his bonnet and
we don't want anyone getting stung.

1195
01:08:45,460 --> 01:08:47,490
Keep your distance.
We're on our way.

1196
01:09:04,660 --> 01:09:06,520
Why were you looking for Hannah?

1197
01:09:07,820 --> 01:09:09,690
I just want a straight answer.

1198
01:09:10,140 --> 01:09:11,939
Mum's tearing herself to bits.

1199
01:09:11,940 --> 01:09:14,079
Is that why you knocked
your dad about last month,

1200
01:09:14,080 --> 01:09:15,380
to get a straight answer?

1201
01:09:15,700 --> 01:09:19,690
You see, we find these
things out eventually.

1202
01:09:20,060 --> 01:09:21,939
Was he lying to me?

1203
01:09:21,940 --> 01:09:24,419
I grovelled to him
because I thought I'd got it wrong.

1204
01:09:24,420 --> 01:09:28,539
Well, as far as we can tell,
he was not having an affair.

1205
01:09:28,540 --> 01:09:30,659
Not with Hannah, anyway.

1206
01:09:30,660 --> 01:09:33,110
Why are you so sure
he was carrying on?

1207
01:09:33,860 --> 01:09:35,160
I'm not.

1208
01:09:38,460 --> 01:09:39,769
Look,

1209
01:09:39,770 --> 01:09:43,559
if I tell you,
you can't tell Mum, OK?

1210
01:09:43,560 --> 01:09:45,469
She's hurt enough as it is.

1211
01:09:45,470 --> 01:09:46,980
All right, come on.

1212
01:09:50,940 --> 01:09:52,330
The day he died,

1213
01:09:52,780 --> 01:09:54,690
a reminder popped up on his phone,

1214
01:09:55,380 --> 01:09:58,470
a booking for a restaurant
in Quayside.

1215
01:09:59,140 --> 01:10:02,200
Now, if he wasn't up to something,
why didn't he tell us about it?

1216
01:10:10,180 --> 01:10:11,480
Aiden...

1217
01:10:12,820 --> 01:10:15,019
Get uniform down to the docks,

1218
01:10:15,020 --> 01:10:17,419
tell them to bring
Gloria Edwards in.

1219
01:10:17,420 --> 01:10:20,579
I think Owen might have been
meeting her at the restaurant.

1220
01:10:20,580 --> 01:10:22,169
And, Helen, get on to Ellie,

1221
01:10:22,170 --> 01:10:23,920
tell her her son's here.

1222
01:10:31,340 --> 01:10:33,059
OK, thank you.

1223
01:10:33,060 --> 01:10:34,369
Ma'am.

1224
01:10:34,370 --> 01:10:37,059
The manager's saying there's
no booking in the name of Edwards.

1225
01:10:37,060 --> 01:10:40,150
However, there was a booking
in the name of Ferris.

1226
01:10:43,900 --> 01:10:46,920
Well, why would Hannah
have been there?

1227
01:10:49,340 --> 01:10:51,989
Unless...
Hold on.

1228
01:10:51,990 --> 01:10:56,719
Helen, did you find a record
of Hannah's mother's suicide?

1229
01:10:56,720 --> 01:10:59,629
I didn't get a call back from
Manchester. I've been chasing...

1230
01:10:59,630 --> 01:11:02,350
So we don't know for
certain she's dead.

1231
01:11:22,100 --> 01:11:23,619
Right.

1232
01:11:23,620 --> 01:11:26,479
Is your mother
Gloria Edwards

1233
01:11:26,480 --> 01:11:29,210
who works with
Owen at the docks?

1234
01:11:31,980 --> 01:11:34,650
You can tell me now or
I can look up the records

1235
01:11:35,580 --> 01:11:38,690
and then arrest you for perverting
the course of justice.

1236
01:11:44,260 --> 01:11:45,560
Yes!

1237
01:11:47,300 --> 01:11:50,000
She went back to work there
in the last year, yes.

1238
01:11:52,420 --> 01:11:54,450
Is Ferris your real name?

1239
01:11:55,180 --> 01:11:57,550
It's the name of the
bloke she married.

1240
01:11:57,940 --> 01:11:59,900
She does use it sometimes.

1241
01:12:01,700 --> 01:12:05,510
Now, why did she come back
up here from Manchester?

1242
01:12:06,180 --> 01:12:10,059
I was here. She wanted
to be close to me.

1243
01:12:10,060 --> 01:12:12,629
Now, you see,
I think she came back up here

1244
01:12:12,630 --> 01:12:15,690
- to reconnect with Owen.
- Maybe.

1245
01:12:16,060 --> 01:12:17,739
Hiding to nothing there.

1246
01:12:17,740 --> 01:12:21,230
I told you, she likes
to torture herself.

1247
01:12:21,790 --> 01:12:23,699
Why did you tell us she was dead?

1248
01:12:23,700 --> 01:12:25,019
I told you.

1249
01:12:25,020 --> 01:12:27,529
Dad didn't want Ellie
knowing anything about me.

1250
01:12:27,530 --> 01:12:29,910
So you were protecting
his family?

1251
01:12:31,700 --> 01:12:35,030
See, I think you're
protecting your mam.

1252
01:12:35,620 --> 01:12:37,250
But from what?

1253
01:12:43,260 --> 01:12:44,889
We've checked with the restaurant.

1254
01:12:44,890 --> 01:12:46,889
There was a birthday
meal booked for three,

1255
01:12:46,890 --> 01:12:48,699
name of Ferris, cake on order.

1256
01:12:48,700 --> 01:12:50,839
And neither you nor Owen turned up.

1257
01:12:50,840 --> 01:12:52,859
I never had any other expectation.

1258
01:12:52,860 --> 01:12:55,919
- So why book it?
- I didn't, Mum did.

1259
01:12:55,920 --> 01:12:58,300
He wasn't interested,
I wasn't.

1260
